Oatmeal baths + Alovera is my savour right now 😂 What a day! (What a month really) After experiencing 10 days of intense PMS+ my hair falling out, I broke out in EM (a reaction rash to the cold-sore virus) + a mouth full of ulcers. The rash only just started to go away when I broke out in hives last night!  WTF WHY! Body! I have money to make + the next two months is filled with 3 research reports + 3 exams! Don't you know anything about timing? 😂 To top it all off today I woke up to my phone been accidentally disconnected by Telstra (how on Earth could that even happen) so I spent over 2 hours at Telstra trying to get it fixed so i could access my bank accounts all while covered head to toe in lovely spots 😂 What's the message? I really don't know! But I do know that no-ones body is perfect. Nope not even a Health Coach, not even an athlete, no ones. Our bodies require constant love, constant nourishment + constant checking in. Wellness is not a destination it's a journey - you've just got to try + enjoy the ride 🙊😂🌸🙌🏼💜⭐️🙏🏼

The concrete jungle of Hong Kong! One of the major transit hubs of Asia. With a 14 hour transit, there was no point in sitting around the airport. So I decided to grab a train and explore the city! ⠀ The wealth and contrast was unreal, something that blew my mind was the sheer number of high rises. Efficient transport makes getting around super easy. Managed to tick of a number of activities in a short period of time. ⠀ Even got lost for a couple of hours and walked right into a major construction site. Ahhh I love new cities. ⠀ If your in transit get out and see the city.

It has been amazing to see Nicola not only persevere and continue her passion for footy through injury, balancing studies, work and family commitments but most importantly when she has never been able to look up to any female football players.  Now she has shown young girls (and grown women) that you can do whatever you want if you are willing to put in the work and it aligns with your values.  It certainly doesn't hurt that she was picked for the All Australian squad and was Collingwood's Best and Fairest winner! She deserves every accolade that comes her way and continues to be the easy going, kind and fearless person I've always known!

💛 The Arts, I freaking love ya. 💛  Tonight I want to appreciate 'The Arts'. Last night I spent an evening at Hamer Hall in Melbourne to see 'The Waifs'. A band I would often see live back in the day,  once when John Butler took my breath away as their support act. A band that I listened to when falling in love with my hubby.  Last night I heard the most incredible music in a space that I was prevlidged to graduate Art School in. A place where I had the most memorable evening spent with my Dad seeing James Taylor whom was always playing in our house growing up (mostly at the end of the night or party) And with all of these memories going through my head then out came the fiddle. All I could hear was one sound in a room of a couple of thousand. An instrument that brings back memories of my beautiful Grandma playing when ever I sang to her. With all of this in my mind and heart I cried like a baby in the concert last night. Seriously. And I'm ok with that. Why? This is the power The Arts can have. Whether it's visual arts, music, film, theatre .....The Arts. I freaking love ya!!! Who's with me?

In a different bowl, mix together grated zucchini, broccoli, garlic, salt, pepper, coriander powder,garam masala powder and saffron powder. 1936. MELBOURNE.—Viewed from one of the numerous bridges that span the River Yarra, a portion of the towered skyline of the capital of Victoria is revealed silhouetted against the evening sky. Most conspicuous are the spires of St. Paul's Cathedral, rising behind the clock tower of the Flinders street railway station. The faint streak of light above the parapet of Queen's Bridge in the middle distance is caused by an electric passenger train crossing the viaduct that runs parallel with the river. #Repost @ottolenghi ・・・ One of many things that I love about living a bicycle oriented life is eating well. But again it's not about quantity but quality. When I'm especially hungry, it's veggies that are my go-to to keep my weight at a healthy BMI.  It wasn't always this way for me.  At the start of my first pregnancy, I was 20kg overweight. I developed severe gestational #diabetes and began injecting insulin 4x a day.  With the help of a dietician who came to my house and my medical team, I managed with diet and exercise. After delivery, I lost 20kg with @weightwatchersaunz. I started the second pregnancy in much better shape and injected once a day and lost the weight again. It was much easier the second time around as I started using a #cargobike as my primary mode of transport to carry my kids.  One of my tips: I weight myself daily as a gauge of how well I'm eating and moving. Female fat loss... Whilst the fundamental principles of diet (energy balance) and exercise (specificity, progressive overload etc) apply universally across genders, there are some significant physiological differences between men and women that dictates how we apply these principles. - 1️⃣Women typically have smaller frames and less muscle mass than males. This means they burn fewer calories per day due to having less body mass. 2️⃣Women store a greater percentage of body fat in their lower extremities, meaning it takes a longer duration to get lean in these areas. 3️⃣Women have 1/7th of the testosterone than males, which means they start with less muscle mass and ultimately build muscle at a slower rate.  4️⃣ The female menstrual cycle influences appetite, energy levels, mood, performance and substrate utilisation. Therefore training and nutrition protocols must be accomodating to these physiological changes at each phase of the cycle! Ingredients  1 lb. linguine or fettuccine  6 tbsp. olive oil  12 oz. mixed mushrooms, thinly sliced  3 cloves garlic, finely chopped  1/4 c. nutritional yeast  2 green onions, thinly sliced on an angle  Directions  Cook linguine as label directs, reserving 3/4 cups pasta cooking water before draining. Return drained linguine to pot.  Meanwhile, in 12" skillet, heat oil on medium-high. Add mushrooms and garlic; cook 5 minutes or until mushrooms are browned and tender, stirring. Transfer to pot with cooked, drained linguine along with nutritional yeast, reserved cooking water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 3/4 teaspoon coarsely ground pepper. Toss until well combined. Garnish with green onions.  Enjoy!

Please have a read of this, thank you @emilyskyefit 🙏🏼 #behappywithyourself ・・・ Sometimes I look like the pic on the left, sometimes times I look like the pic on the right. - I don't always have abs or look lean and I'm never "perfect". .  So many people are aiming for this idea of "perfection"... but what exactly is perfection?  I used to beat myself up for not being perfect (whatever that is). I'd actually feel like my "worth" was less if I didn't look a certain way. My goal at one stage was to get rid of my belly fat so that when I sat I'd have no "rolls" - now I see how ridiculous and superficial I was being. Yes there's no denying, I like to look good, as most people do but it's not healthy when it becomes an obsession and your "self worth" is attached to your appearance. I've just returned from being overseas for a month. I ate what I wanted and enjoyed it, I also gained a bit of extra body fat which isn't a big deal because my lifestyle nowadays isn't about restricting myself & I like it that way. 😝#noregrets . Life isn't perfect and neither are we. I love myself no matter how I look and it's this self love that motivates me to make changes in my life so I can feel my best... like exercising and eating nutritious food (& treats for mental health hehe). 😝 I was once sitting at a fitness shoot and was told by someone (while pointing at my belly) "Fitness models don't have belly rolls when they sit" - I was so upset about this & felt so inadequate and this only led to me being more obsessed with being "perfect" or as "lean" as I could be. Nowadays I know better. My priority is how I feel mentally and physically and I won't sacrifice that to look a certain way OR to get the approval from anyone else! Please consider what goes into a photograph you see online or in magazines... and also what goes into looking a certain way, for example; posing, angles, lighting & even photoshopping! A lot of what we see in these images is not "healthy" or "realistic" and comparing ourselves will never do us any good. Focus on your health - mental and physical and focus on being YOUR best.

With so many cafes opening across Melbourne, you have to stand out from the crowd for people to be lining up out the door, and No. 19 certainly has the X-factor.  The striking interior draws you in with its natural light, hand-painted teal tiles, brass details, and concrete surfaces all of which come together to pay homage to Greek delicatessens that populated Melbourne in the 1950s.  Owned by local couple Domanic and Diana Caruso, the space is the creation of local design firm Biasol. "Our concept was inspired by the Greek delicatessens that flourished around Melbourne in the 1950s," said the Biasol team. "Materially, concrete surfaces - the counter, walls and floor - give the space a warmth and sophistication." Read more on neoskosmos.com

So this week I finished a project with an inspiring company @timeivchangewatches who are creating change through their collection of handcrafted watches.  Their entire collection is made from vegan leather including a range of pineapple leather "Pinatex" watches. Their watch cases are designed out of 100% recycled aluminium. And to top it off, they give back 20% of their profits to 9 organisations pushing for positive change. From sanctuaries to vegan emergency relief operations.  This project really opened my eyes up to the harm that leather production has not just on the animals whose lives it takes. But on the people who work in the tanneries and the surrounding communities. Not to mention l the strain it puts on our environment due to the huge water resources animal leather production needs.  Time IV Change took the idea of  creating #veganwatches and made it a reality. They achieved their kickstarter campaign in just 7 days. And now they're the world's first vegan watch company!  Just one year on, their watches sell out in just hours! And they have the very nice problem of not being able to keep up with demand. 👌🏽 It was a pleasure to write their story and help architect a user experience for this positive  movement.  And if you'd like to find out more about their story and watch range head to: www.timeivchange.com.au  #bethechange

Brooklyn Depot Melbourne is a New York-inspired sports bar just off the north end of Hardware Lane, with a large central bar surrounded by benches, tables and booths.  The Brooklyn Classic burger is their base model burger with everything after that getting quite extreme with pork belly, lamb, pulled chicken, turkey and mushroom burgers all on offer.  Brooklyn Classic was difficult to photograph. It comes with lettuce, tomato and Depot special sauce, but fillings are quite scarce and everything is hidden inside that massive, seeded milk bun. The beef was rich and juicy, perfectly cooked and well seasoned. The cheese was amazing and gooey, melted over the top. The sauce was plentiful and gave a great tang. But salad items were lost, not crunchy, and rather pointless here. The milk bun had a lot of flavour in itself and the sweetness was slightly overpowering for this simple burger.  A side of fries can be added to your burger order. Not shown in this photo, I also ordered a basket of Phat Chips which were absolutely delicious, crunchy outside, fluffy inside, and seasoned with plenty of chilli sea salt for a spicy zing.  The venue has a great vibe, the food is delicious and service was great. I look forward to trying some other burger options here later in the year, or just popping in for drinks.  #burger #food #melbourne #newyork #sportsbar

Ogni persona è unica e, quindi, possiede un proprio concetto dell’amore. La nostra idea dell’amore riflette chi siamo, i nostri desideri, i nostri valori, le nostre aspettative e il nostro modo di vivere le relazioni. La parola “Amore” è tra le più usate nel linguaggio comune. Se ne parla di continuo: tra le persone, in televisione, sulle riviste, sui siti.Sull’amore si scrivono messaggi, poesie, libri…eppure sembra proprio difficile dare una definizione univoca dell’Amore che metta tutti d’accordo. Per esempio, se cercassimo una definizione “obiettiva” dell’amore su qualsiasi dizionario, leggeremmo: “L’amore è un sentimento intenso e profondo di affetto, simpatia ed adesione, rivolto verso una persona, un animale, un oggetto o verso un concetto, un ideale”. Ma una tale frase, cosa dice di noi, delle nostre passioni amorose, dei nostri tormenti e delle nostre gioie? Una definizione oggettiva non rende al 100% il nostro modo di vivere l’amore. Se ne parla di continuo forse proprio perché il concetto dell’amore è davvero inafferrabile. Who is the real Aussie?  This picture was taken during my trip to Melbourne, and there is a context to it.  The cameleers were camel drivers, mostly from Afghanistan, India and Pakistan and they helped explore the outback and helped establish rail networks. They basically ran the outback for 70 years and not many people know they existed.  This particular gentleman is Monga Khan. He applied for an exemption from the white Australia policy about 100 years ago. He is particularly heroic and symbolic in highlighting struggle of all those who made it possible to make Australia the diverse land that it is.  #australia #aussiesofinstagram #aussie #history #melbourne #victoria #afghanistan #India #Indian #historic #heroic #hero #struggle #hustle #diversity #culture #nation #story #storytelling #streetart #streetphotography #mobilephotography #travelphotography #travel #traveller #travelling #travels #lifelessons

I LOVE hot cross buns and I was really excited to see a new flavour at my local @BakersDelight this Easter! They’ve spiced up an old favourite with their new Apple & Cinnamon Hot Cross Buns and to celebrate, I’m sharing a super delicious recipe using them with you all! Ear mark this one for Easter morning guys – it’s delicious and easy!  Recipe: Serves 2 2 Baker’s Delight Apple and Cinnamon Hot Cross Buns, sliced in half 2/3 cup ricotta 2 tsp maple syrup 2 tbs chopped walnuts 1 egg, beaten with a dash of milk 1 tbs rapadura sugar 1 tsp cinnamon  Place Baker’s Delight Apple and Cinnamon Hot Cross Buns into egg mixture for 30 seconds to soak, turning them over. Place straight into a non-stick frypan on medium heat, fry until golden brown then flip onto the other side and repeat. While it’s cooking, combine ricotta, maple and walnuts in a bowl. In another bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon. When the buns are golden all over, dip the top into the sugar and cinnamon mixture then layer some ricotta mix between the two pieces of bun. MELBOURNE // @studio_twocan is a creative studio, managed by sisters, Maddie and Becc Sharrock. Every Studio Twocan piece is individually handcrafted with care and precision. Their cement ceramics range was refined over two years. It has taken time to  perfect their products, which shows their dedication and commitment to quality of design and manufacture. They colour the cement using pigment to create an organic layering inspired by Australian landscapes. Each piece is polished with natural oils, sealing the cement with a satin finish. This process celebrates imperfections and ensures that each piece is unique. Put these out the other day and already down to my last. Must get more stat!  When unattended environmental and economic crises lead to social chaos, not even gated communities are safe. In a night of fire and death Lauren Olamina, a minister's young daughter, loses her family and home and ventures out into the unprotected American landscape. But what begins as a flight for survival soon leads to something much more: a startling vision of human destiny... and the birth of a new faith. About the Author Octavia E. Butler was the first black woman to come to international prominence as a science fiction writer. Incorporating powerful, spare language and rich, well-developed characters, her work tackled race, gender, religion, poverty, power, politics, and science in a way that touched readers of all backgrounds. Butler was a towering figure in life and in her art and the world noticed; highly acclaimed by reviewers, she received numerous awards, including a MacArthur "genius" grant, both the Hugo and Nebula awards, the Langston Hughes Medal, as well as a PEN Lifetime Achievement award. #embiggenbooks #books #melbourne #scifi #bookstagram

Cauliflower Buffalo Wings  Ingredients: - 1 head of cauliflower, washed and broken up into small florets - 1 tsp extra virgin olive oil - 1 tsp garlic powder - 1 tsp onion powder - 1 tsp paprika - 1 tsp chilli powder - 1/2 tsp kosher salt - 1/4 hot sauce (your choice)  Directions: - preheat oven 200 C - Oil baking pan with olive oil - Combine hot sauce, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, chilli powder and salt in a small bowl - Toss cauliflower and distribute evenly. Making sure all cauliflower is is coated in spices - Bake for 18-20mins - Serve with homemade ranch dressing.  Enjoy peeps 👌

Did you know that Saganaki is Greek in origin? It is a kind of hors d'oeuvre that is named for the frying pan in which it is prepared. The word is a diminutive of the word "sagani," a frying pan with two handles. 🥘 Interestingly, "sagani" is also a borrowed word from the Turkish "sahan," meaning a copper dish. Kirsty Hawkes is an interpretive artist based in Warrnambool. Kirsty and her practice are both unique. This photograph titled ‘Unicorns are real’, explores the ephemeral, surreal world of dreams and their connection to the world of the day to day. It also raises questions of the feminine and the notion of the mask, to be alien and strange and barefoot in the surf. . Ok that was one of the strangest comedy shows I have ever seen... (spoiler alert and trigger warning) It starts off with the comedian jumping on a treadmill while in the background on a projector he is being chased by a gorilla. The monkey represents the primitive part of is mind, his fears. He stays on the treadmill for the whole show and does comedy. But what starts out as comedy becomes a story about his life and how he was date raped... and it is a serious story, presented as a comedy. It has it's funny moments but it was so contrasting, and the fact he was on his treadmill getting healthy and trying to be positive made it all the more weird. I thought he was brave and it was a clever show, it was just totally unexpected. I also liked that he used comedy to explain a difficult subject that obviously had a profound effect on him. There was recordings of his therapy sessions among other things. He even made a point of saying "I know this is a comedy festival, I was hesitant but they insisted". It was an interesting show and unlike anything I have ever seen. I'm not surprised it has won awards... #comedy #Melbourne #survivor #acmi

Portrait 189/1000: Dave Shepherd. Dave is one of the owners of @essenza_cafes, a brilliant little cafe in Healesville's main street. The space the cafe now occupies was once a walkway between two storefronts, and it's now a beautiful, cosy cafe space with excellent coffee and a place to sit out of the heat and noise of the main street. I remember going there after it opened and thinking it was a very Melbourne-esque cafe for the town, and a great thing to have open. Since then, I've had countless coffees there and gotten to know Dave and the staff there pretty well. Brad, one of the baristas there, was my 100th portrait. Dave's always been lovely to catch up with over that time, and I barrelled up to him on the street a last year and asked if I could take his portrait for the project. He generously obliged and we took this right out the front of the cafe. Thank you for your time, David! Keep up the excellent work (and coffee!).

A fleeting trip to Melbourne enabled me to capture an iconic city feature... The Exhibition Fountain designed by sculptor John Hochgurtel. The fountain is also known as Hochgurtel fountain. It was built on the south side of the Royal Exhibition Building in Carlton Gardens - a world heritage site. Standing at ten metres tall, the colossal fountain has characteristics of Victorian-era architecture. Weight loss isn’t solely about creating change for the sake of looking better and functioning better. How we FEEL in our own skin phenomenally impacts how we interact with the world and the people in it. This mind-body connection dominos into every other component of our lives – relationships, work, family… not to mention energy, mood, concentration and our ability to react to problems…  This is what Peter Graham realised about his own life, reflecting back on the experience of completing the same 16-week program I did. “I was over 100kg, working more than 100 hours a week and feeling overwhelmed, unfulfilled and disillusioned with the path my family and I had chosen.” ✨ I wanted to share his story because it’s such a beautiful example of how powerful change can be in our lives when we finally decide to take the plunge ✨ "30 days in I was still working more than 100 hours a week and with the same responsibilities, BUT I was like a completely different guy. “Wow, you’re fixed!” said my mum on first sight, noticing colour and life back in my face. I had released 10kg of fat, was handling stress a LOT better and had the clarity of mind to make better life decisions and be truly present with my family.” 🎉 As for his results, Peter lost 22kg, went from 35% to 11.8% body fat and dropped 2.4kg of visceral fat 🎉 "3 years into this journey and the last 16 weeks have been the most transformative on so many levels. I’ve smashed through limiting beliefs, created positive daily habits and now feel healthier, fitter, stronger, happier and more connected in my relationships. But biggest of all, I’m starting to feel more in alignment with the fit, healthy guy looking back at me in the mirror.” #thenewfitvision

Check out this super easy Apple & Cinnamon Hot Cross Bun recipe from @naturally_nutritious ___________________________________  I LOVE hot cross buns and I was really excited to see a new flavour at my local @BakersDelight this Easter! They’ve spiced up an old favourite with their new Apple & Cinnamon Hot Cross Buns and to celebrate, I’m sharing a super delicious recipe using them with you all! Ear mark this one for Easter morning guys – it’s delicious and easy!  Recipe: Serves 2 2 Baker’s Delight Apple and Cinnamon Hot Cross Buns, sliced in half 2/3 cup ricotta 2 tsp maple syrup 2 tbs chopped walnuts 1 egg, beaten with a dash of milk 1 tbs rapadura sugar 1 tsp cinnamon  Place Baker’s Delight Apple and Cinnamon Hot Cross Buns into egg mixture for 30 seconds to soak, turning them over. Place straight into a non-stick frypan on medium heat, fry until golden brown then flip onto the other side and repeat. While it’s cooking, combine ricotta, maple and walnuts in a bowl. In another bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon. When the buns are golden all over, dip the top into the sugar and cinnamon mixture then layer some ricotta mix between the two pieces of bun. The Zookeeper's Wife, starring Jessica Chastaino, tells the incredible true story of Antonina Zabinska who ran the Warsaw Zoo with her husband Dr. Jan Zabinski.  When Poland is invaded by the Nazis, Antonina and Jan work with the Resistance to shelter hundreds of displaced Jews, risking their own lives in the process.  We're holding a special advance screening at Classic of The Zookeeper's Wife to mark International Holocaust Remembrance Day. Join us at 3pm on Sunday 23 April: tickets on sale now at the box office and online.

Just do. ➖➖➖➖➖ I constantly surprise myself. I sit back and think 'man, it would be awesome to breath a little' - followed up by action, action and more action. I fill up my plate more and more and do more and more and still - some people like to tell me what they think I should do. The key here however, those people who are telling me what to do - are not doing themselves. So until they put themselves in your shoes or actually risk it a little, open up their minds a little or even realise that their way isn't the be all and end all and actually realise that we are all unique and the beautiful thing about life is - you can do whatever the hell you want - then just keep doing. Be obsessed with what makes you happy regardless. Amazing things can happen at the drop of a hat if you just do! Anyone in your life right now who seems to tell you how to live? I suggest it's time to remove yourself from then! 💯 💯  SMPT - your journey, my passion  www.stephenmiller.com.au

Pineapple Shrimp fried rice bowl recipe: Ingredients:  1 1/2 cups (uncooked) brown rice 1 tsp oil 1.25 lb shrimp, shelled and deveined, (1lb after peeled) chopped into chunks 1 1/2 cups fresh pineapple, cut into small chunks 5 large scallions, chopped 3 cloves garlic, minced 1 fresh chili pepper or jalepeno, chopped 2 tsp soy sauce (or more to taste) 1 tbsp fish sauce  cilantro for garnish Directions:  Cook brown rice according to package directions and set aside to cool. Cut a pineapple in half and hollow out both halves to make two bowls.  Heat a nonstick wok on high heat; when hot add oil. Add shrimp and cook a few minutes until almost cooked though.  Add chilli/scallops/garlic.  Saute about a minute, then add the rice and pineapple and stir a few times. Add soy sauce and fish sauce, stir to mix all the ingredients and cook another 30 seconds. GRAVITY TOWER | Occupying a commanding position, this signature 29 storey tower presents a singular, iridescent form, whose striking façade geometries emphasise the buildings glittering textural presence. Tiers of angular, syncopated add a continuously altering expression, where light, shade and reflection evolve throughout the day to create a dynamic, shifting visual quality. A sensational collection of rooftop relaxation areas inlude a Teppanyaki grill and BBQ, private dining and kitchen, outdoor cinema, and spa with incredible views from Port Phillip Bay to the city skyline. Spacious 1 and 2 bedroom apartments offer great internal space.  With construction finishing in July, get in quick to save on stamp duty.  Prices start from $449,000 for 1 bedroom appartments. ”The World's 50 Best Restaurants 2017”  毎年ある世界のベストレストランが発表される表彰会が今年も開催された！  今年はメルボルン 王立博物館で。  今年1位はNYのEleven Madison Park！！！ イタリアン、フレンチ、和食という枠じゃない。  ボーダレスな料理、ダイニング、レストランばかりがランクイン。  ペルー、ブラジル、インド、シンガポールたくさんの国のレストラン。  でも、どのレストランのシェフもその国に誇りを持ち、その国の料理を革新し、世界に発信していっている。  オーナー、シェフだけが喜ぶんじゃない。  チームで喜び、チームで泣く。 分かち合えるのは日頃からそういうレストランのチームづくりをしているから。  こういうチームを作りたい。  そして、絶対この舞台に立ちたい！！！ レストランとして名前を呼ばれたい。  自分1人じゃ成し得ないけど、今は自分ができることを確実にやろう。 夢は叶えるもの！ #restaurant #worlds50best  #melbourne  #wasyoku  #dream

AND THIS LITTLE FELICIA IS GOING SOMEWHERE......... 🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧 My cake lovers, the time has come to tell you that I am moving to LONDON! So. Yes. Where do I begin? I decided when I got back from Europe last year that I wanted to see more, live somewhere else and really shake my life up a bit. As some of you know, Miss Trixie is my little side gig. Full time, I am an events producer. And the thing is? I love cakes. And I love production. And I want more. So I came to the decision to make a move over to the U.K. In no ways does this mean this is the end of Miss Trixie. In fact, I see this as the beginning. New opportunities. People to meet. Things to see. I'm really hoping that once I'm on my feet in London, I can start spoiling Londoners with my cakes like I have done with loyal Melbournians for the last couple of years. So be sure to hit me up if you're over in London! Or if you're looking for a cake making all star producer 😏. You'll obviously be able to see all my travels and updates here on Insta, so hang tight for the ride. Oh, and if there are any amazing cake places that you think I must check out when I land, comment below! Because I crave cake every second of every day. Thanks for the support cake lovers, buckle up! ♥️♥️

我曾經對好友說，我很享受一個人搭清晨巴士的時刻，因為那是個我能與自己內心對話的過程。清晨讓人感覺美好，是全新的開始，讓人充滿無限希望和動力，而我喜歡這樣的感覺。  曾經在前去工作45分鐘的路途中，我總是喜歡挑選第一排靠窗的位子。車窗外一幕幕飛逝的景色能讓我的思緒慢慢的沈澱，讓我能思考很多平日沒時間去細想的事情。思緒偶爾會飄得遠遠的，很多曾經在書裡看到的美麗詞彙會慢慢的在腦海中成形，組成一句句貼近我內心世界的文字。有時候我會選擇把它們給紀錄下來，有時候會任它們在腦海裡自由暢行，隨意翱翔，讓我在文字拼湊與思緒中感受到平日裡感受不到的美好。  那45分鐘的車程裡，我選擇不與周邊乘客交流，或是避開任何交流的機會。對我來說，那時刻是我獨有的空間，我選擇擁抱自己與美好的交會，那讓我回到曾經有無限想像力和詩情畫意的歲月裡。  #那曾經和詩情畫意和憂愁善感劃上等號的我 #australia #melbourne #sunnyday #travel #vacation #summer #holiday #instapic #instadaily #instastyle #ootd #outfit #fashion #coordinate #mixnmatch #instafashion #instastyle #backtonatur #wanderlust #flashpacker #philipisland #churchillisland #igersmalaysia #igmalaysia #life

I should not be allowed within a million miles of a bookshop! The Melbourne haul includes vampires (unexpected!) the eerie (very!) the romantic, travel and two incredibly special ones.  The Observer's Book of Dogs  gifted by the insightful, funny, very special Michele (Foss) @cypressfoss who perhaps listened to Minty and Eloise when they whispered "she loves dogs" or just really has connected with my IG posts as I have hers. Thank you Foss I'll treasure it. Then Beyond the Rock by the generous, talented, loving Janelle @janellemcculloch_author who, having signed well over 50 books, believes she made an error on mine because she did it mid hug and avid catch up chat. Janelle I love that you were not on auto pilot, that you cared enough to make it special, that no one else has this inscription and every time I see it I will remember that moment we connected. Believe me when I say it could not be more perfect my dear friend. Thank you my darling daughter @katvwil for three beautiful days xxx #books#beyondtherock#friends#romance#melbourne#thebestthreedays

Four GEICO Skytypers performing at last weekend's Melbourne Air and Space Show. This was actually the second image I took all day, and it ended up being one of my favorites. Photo taken Saturday April 1, 2017. Following description of the aircraft is credit geicoskytypers.com: "The GEICO Skytypers fly the SNJ-2 version of the aircraft. This model has an enlarged 180 gallon fuel tank allowing the aircraft to operate for more than four hours.  Other unique design elements of this particular aircraft include: a decrease of eight inches in the overall length, a larger round rudder,  and a free-castering tail wheel. Each plane weighs 5500 pounds and utilizes a 600hp Pratt and Whitney R-1340-AN-1, 9 cylinder radial engine.  This remarkable and versatile aircraft was an evolution of the NAA’s BC-1 basic combat trainer. 174 BC-1s were first produced in 1937 for the U.S. Army Aircorp.  These aircraft also utilized fixed landing gear. The BC-1 was designed by North American as a low-cost trainer with all the characteristics of a high-speed fighter. While not as fast as a fighter, it was simple to maintain and repair, had more maneuverability and was easier to handle than previous models. A pilot’s airplane, it could roll, loop, spin, snap, and vertical roll. It was designed to provide the best possible training in all types of tactics, from ground strafing to bombardment to aerial dog-fighting. The aircraft also contained versatile equipment such as bomb racks, blind flying instrumentation, gun and standard cameras, fixed and flexible guns, and just about every other device that military pilots had to operate at that time."

Trying these Raspberry Acai Bliss Balls this morning 😍 RECIPE: 1 cup frozen raspberries 10 medjool dates, seeds removed 1 cup raw cashews 2 cups desiccated coconut 1 teaspoon vanilla extract pinch of salt 10g Acai powder  Place the ingredients into your food processor and pulse at high speed until the mixture is broken down, well combined and sticking together. Use your hands to shape the mixture into balls. Either leave the balls as they are or roll in coconut or cacao or cocoa or drizzle with melted dark chocolate. Place in the fridge to set. Portrait 195/1000: Joel Hawting. Joel is a pastor at Liberty Family Church in Healesville. He and I first met when the church was running events to raise money as part of World Vision Australia's 40 Hour Famine, and because he's involved in events and projects around town, we end up talking pretty often and he's been in the paper a few times as a result. This photo was actually taken for a newspaper article, because Joel and several other people in town had made a team for Movember Foundation Australia. This photo was taken at the start of the month, with a bit of shadow on his face; his team had a goal of growing horseshoe moustaches, and grow them they did. Thanks for your time, Joel!  Note: My photo schedule got waaaay out of whack and this got posted the other day. My bad!

I've spent years building up on a neglected frame and cracks are showing more often as time passes. Mostly using exercises that have fostered poor joint control. Zinc testing. Zinc deficiencies is more common than we realise. It can lead to dozens of health conditions. Many people are unaware of the importance of this mineral. Conditions such as anxiety, depression, chronic fatigue & lingering illnesses, heart conditions, slow wound healing, gut health & irritable bowles can all be improved with an in increase zinc. Thumbs up if you agree! Comment if you don't ;) WHY YOU MUST STOP ICING INJURIES... (Note: This is completely not related to ice baths, which is very beneficial.) The research is in: According to large studies the concept of ‘R.I.C.E’ and Anti-Inflammatories to manage acute injuries actually INTERFERES with your healing process and creates more inflammatory waste congestion.  Think about this: The first thing I always teach you is: You’re a perfect healing machine, your body has designed over millions of years. It is much smarter than any intervention or ‘cure’ we externally apply. When you give your body it’s requirements for life (The right movement, mobility and spinal alignment, nutrition, sleep and mental state) - it will be a perfect healing & performing machine.  WHY THE BASIC IDEA OF ICING IS WRONG: - ICING ASSUMES THE NATURAL HEALING PROCESS OF YOUR BODY (INFLAMMATION) IS A MISTAKE. Icing reduces inflammation. But EVERY medical text book will tell you: There are 3 phases of healing: Inflammation, Repair, Remodelling. The inflammatory process is your HEALING process - it brings healing nutrients in and then movement and pressure on the area pumps injury waste out through your lymphatic vessels. (Healing nutrients in, waste out.) - ICING CAUSES BACK-FLOW AND MORE CONGESTION OF LYMPHATIC FLUID. ie. It SLOWS the CLEARING of inflammatory waste! Lots of studies show this. - ICING AND NSAIDS (ANTI-INFLAMMATORIES) INTERFERE WITH THE NERVE REGULATION OF INJURED TISSUE AND THE PARTICLES (PROSTAGLANDINS/MACROPHAGES ETC THAT COME TO HEAL THE SITE.  So what to take from this? If you’re injured, be aware that icing SLOWS your body’s intelligent healing process. Instead try: 1. Keep the area as mobile as possible, within pain threshold. If you leave it immobile, the inflammatory waste sits there, increases pressure (creates pain), and later clogs up into scar tissue.  2. Periodically compress the area with a band/strap. A voodoo band is AMAZING for this. See my mobility vids to see hove they work. This will help clear out the waste products. Thoughts? QUESTIONS? Leave them in the comments!

M I L K  T H E  C O W 🐄  Having heard amazing things about this reputable fromagerie, we got together a group of girls to go get us some wine and cheese (yassssss!). Their Carlton location is home is a massive five metre cheese cabinet with over 150 cheeses on offer. Inside was packed, so our lovely waiter Lucas made sure we were comfortable outside with some super soft blankets.  You can opt for a cheese flight board matched with your drink of choice here, but this time around we decided to build our own. Top cheese of the night was definitely the oak smoked cheddar, but if you're into soft cheeses, loved the triple cream brie. Prosciutto was thinly sliced and a great addition, we also recommend the quince!  Love that this place is open until 1am, great to sit down and catch up with friends at. We do recommend asking for paired drinks as after selecting our own drinks we realised they were overshadowed by how good the cheese was. Service is knowledgable and super friendly. We really enjoyed ourselves and will be back!  Atmosphere: 3.75/5  Price: $50 for two people  Food: 4/5

We took advantage of the warmth today to check out the new Maritime Cove Community Park playground at Perce White Reserve in Port Melbourne. It's covered in sand and has sand play stations and a loopy loop slide similar to Ron Barassi Snr Park playground, and rope courses, climbing frames and water play stations similar to Royal Park playground. These new modern playground designs are awesome! I was surprised at how big the place was! There are so many different stations to play at...and even exercise equipment for adults right at the end! Here are my kids at the toddler sand play section. There is easy parking right in front of the playground, and a great bonus is that Sandridge Beach is literally meters away! We'll definitely be back ❤️

There will never be a time I will ever get over having twins. There will never be a time that I don't look at this perfect bunch and think..'wow! I can't believe I made all that!'. As much as they test me and push my boundaries into areas I never knew existed, they have taught me more than I anticipated.  They taught me that life prior to children was actually never hard, I just never knew what hard was... they taught me that I can actually survive on 4-5 hours sleep...regularly,  they taught me to be stronger emotionally, they taught me what self control actually is...especially when you scream 'FFS!!' 57469 times a day and it's all said in your mind,  they taught me that not only can I run? I can do it pushing 50kg,  they taught me to juggle 2000 things at a time,  to still be happy when I cook food that they say is 'disgusting', they taught me that washing my hair only twice a week is still ok,  They taught me to cherish moments, to be grateful for my and their health, and oh so much more.  I sometimes sit by their beds at night and promise them to be better or try harder tomorrow, and each day I wake up, I remind myself to always be better than any situation gives me, especially if it is too much for me to handle at any given moment.  I am loving holidays and they are with me all the time and the rush of kinder is not being missed!  But I look at this picture? And I'm just so proud, as these 3 little babies are my biggest accomplishment yet. . . . . #onestongmum #meplus3 #babies #twinmum #lifelessons #parenting #grateful #family #3babies #melbourne #melbournemum #fitmum

5 years ago I was lucky to be invited to cook a dinner at Attica with this wonderful person. We were planning a dish with skate to be a part of the menu and as the size and type of skate available to us was causing us trouble Ben admitted to me in a cautious and polite way that honestly, he wouldn't have put that on his own menu since it was threatened by extinction. I felt I had to take it off the menu, anything else would have been disrespectful, and we cooked a dish on beautiful local mussels instead.  Once I got home I started studying the subject and realizing how little informed I actually was. Skate never saw the menu since and that incident shaped me and inspired me to take more responsibility.  Yesterday night I had the pleasure of dining at @atticamelbourne again and another wonderful experience there of passion and professionalism reminded me once again how keeping true to yourself while working hard for your dreams is the biggest achievement to strive for.  Keep inspiring @benshewry 🙏🏻 Thank you.  #melbourne #australia #worlds50best #sustainability #cooking #respect

Flashback Friday - Award Winning Packaging  Back in 2005, Bayly partnered with International Consolidated Business to develop an ergonomic spray bottle that allows users to spray a uniquely formulated toilet-cleaning agent in all areas of the toilet.  Said the judges of the 2006 Australian Packaging Awards: "This novel ‘inverted trigger’ design is a great improvement in functionality, effectively alleviating aching wrists from cleaning awkward toilet bowls. Easy to use upside-down and far more comfortable to hold than competitor brands, this winning solution is also a packaging breakthrough.  The ‘proud’ styling of this new bent-neck bottle silhouette echoes the boldness of the concept, and almost animates the product to great advantage at point of sale. This product actually looks ready for action.  #Bayly #Productdesign #Melbourne #Packaging #innovation  Learn more about this project here: http://www.bayly.com.au/our-work-as-a-product-design-company/portfolio/showcase/90-award-winning-packaging-design

🌺Why your skin needs Vitamin A🌺  Since our body does not make Vitamin A, our skin becomes deficient over time. In particular, the sun depletes the skin of Vitamin A and this is one of the reasons those who super-expose their skin to sun damage age faster than those who do not (and another reason to always use broad-spectrum SPF every single day, rain, hail or shine). Vitamin A helps to- •Smooth both wrinkles and fine lines •Increases elasticity and collagen production •Evens out skin texture and skin tone •Improves acne by regulating oil flow •Stimulates natural cellular turnover  read the full article from @cosbeauty http://www.cosbeauty.com.au/beauty/skin-needs-vitamin/ • • #vitamina #serum #healthy #skincare #skinhealth #melbourne #melbourneskin #cosbeauty #morningtonpeninsula #rosebud #skinastute

I don't have a "morning routine" in terms of exercise or mindfulness, but I intend on finding something that works for me. The plan is I'll pick all of that up as soon as I can bend down to pick all of that up.... Finished the 100km out in Wesburn at 3am this morning in 19 hours 29 minutes. We were the fourth fastest female team out of 161 teams. Overall we ranked 41 of 612 teams which is very cool considering we don't run any of the trail. We lost Emily to injury at the 72km mark which was awful but in the hot conditions all four of us were ridiculously proud of our individual efforts. Delirious and sore, but proud. Thank you to everyone for their support-it meant the world xx

📻📻📻📻📻 . A few tasty hints for what to cook this weekend from Joanne... . Sweet Potatoes - an over supply this week has seen the prices drop dramatically. A wonderfully #healthy vegetable, it can replace regular potatoes, or even pumpkin in most recipes. Try the white and red varieties if you're feeling adventurous! . Horseradish - the first pick of the new season has arrived, just in time for Jewish Passover. It's a staple in traditional Jewish custom. But it should also be a staple in your pantry because it's packed with a range of vitamins and minerals... and it's delicious too! . Quinces - you know it's autumn when the quinces arrive 🍁Keen jam and paste makers should note that the quince's pectin content is always higher at the start of the season. So the earlier you get on it, the better it will turn out . Pears - we're starting to see a handover from the #summer varieties, like William pears, to the #winter varieties like Packham and Burre Bosc. William are alway nice and sweet late in the season, but can be a little flowery. You can probably find better quality in the Packhams or Bosc from now on... . #fruit #vegetables #local #seasonal #delicious #fresh #healthyeating #healthyfood #food #instafood #nutritious #nutrition #wellbeing #vegeterian #vegan #homecooked #homemade #recipe #organic #melbourne #melbourneeats #melbournefood #melbournefoodie #shoplocal #eatlocal

When you decide to be raw, authentic and share yourself on social media - you have to open up to criticism. Now, I don't even have many followers or claim to have people that are interested in my life anymore than they are yours - but my choices, my decisions - inspire some, confuse many, and cause concern (it seems) for others. There are some people in my home town who have been asking my friends if I am "okay", based on my Instagram posts. I can only assume these concerned folks are talking about the kink posts, and perhaps the idea that I've sold all my material belongings and jet setted across the world without much warning. You may not understand me, you may not understand my decisions - and I know, as a mature and clear minded person, that you are not asking to cause drama, but because you are interested, you are intrigued. You are curious. You want to know more. So, just in case there is anyone else who wants to question my friends about my wellbeing, here it is - I am doing great, I am safe, I am empowered, I am empowered sexually (and if you don't understand that, it's okay☺️), I am happy and authentic and I feel very free. If anyone is intrigued or concerned, or wants to ask me any questions then - I am an open book :) And please, remember - we are all interesting in our own unique ways, we all have different realities, and if something intrigues you or threatens your reality, you do not have to understand it, you do not have to make sense of it, but you do need to be kind and respectful of other people and their choices. 😘 #melbourne #kind #respect #peace #love

Swipe → to see all  I've been seeing a fair few of these posts lately. The general concensus on dieting is that it must be this tedious, unenjoyable process of self torture which eventually leads to loss of complience via binging or just forfeiting your diet.  Understand that progress is made through consistency over time. Weight loss and weight gain are merely a game of numbers. Calories in vs calories out, and the manipulation of macronutrients.  What you eat is not important when it comes to building muscle and losing fat. The ratio of fat, carbohydrate and protein intake and total calorie intake are what is important.  If you want to lose weight, you must be in a calorie deficit.  If you want to gain weight, you need to be in a calorie surplus.  There are plenty of calculators out there to estimate your starting macros. However, undersrsnd that this is a process of trial and error, and more often than not, your macros will change on a week to week basis.  If you are unsure as where to start. I reccomend you start by merely tracking what you are eating now. Track what intake is over a few days and compare those days. Take an average for what you currently hit. Begin to understand what is going into your body.... this can be good practice for when you need to refine the process.  Use an app: I use MyFitnessPal for my macro counting.  Ask for help: I run a fexible dieting coaching service. Inquires via the email in the bio of my profile.  Feel free to tag a friend you believe would benefit from this advice. My main goal here is to educate. I wish to reach as many people as possible.  Let's all smash our goals together, and enjoy the process.

My exhibition 'Friends and Beasts' is now in full swing at Tacit Contemporary Art in Abbotsford. It's a show that celebrates my love of animals with classic black and white images capturing a moment of connection. There is also a series of smaller abstract studies that explore the beauty of feathers, fur, skin and scales. These samples show just a few of the framed and unframed limited edition fine art prints for sale. The gallery closes for Easter between 10-18 April, so today would be the perfect opportunity to see the exhibition between 11am and 5pm. Enjoy!

The Northcote Social Club started life as the Commercial Hotel. Following the Maritime Strike of 1890, during the height of Labour-Capital tensions in 1891, the hotel played host to the first meeting of the Northcote Workingman's Democratic Association. The organisation was dedicated to 'mutual assistance, promotion of a brotherhood of affection, unanimity of thought and action in matters affecting the social and political welfare of the working classes and the propagation of an Australian democracy.' The association became the first branch of Trades Hall's Progressive Political League, a precursor to the Labor Party. Eventually it was known to me that Chad Mcqueen (Steve's son) was coming down to Australia for a classic motorshow so hell and highwater I had to get it signed, eventually I found Chad and he signed it for me, he didn't at first realise that this watch was very significant historically to his father but once I explained it to him he was impressed! The locals told me this tree fell last year after a storm hit the island . . . Some said to let it go. A man and his friend said it still had life in it and to give it a chance. The ones who said let it go didn't bother to help when the two men decided to help it back up. They packed sand bags around it and put the tree between two sticks. It was droopy and lifeless. But everyday in between their shifts they would stop by, talk to it and water it. For months it looked helpless, but then the same tree started to grow leaves. And it eventually started looking like this. They told me, it should be back to its old self, if not stronger in a few more months.  I loved hearing this story. In this story, the perseverance of the tree and the faith these two men had in it really inspired me to keep going and have faith in my journey. Some days I feel unsure of where I'm headed, but I guess if we were to figure it all out today. Where would be the fun in that?

It was a long time dreaming it. And creating it was another painful time. Perhaps dreaming and creating always associated with growing pain. It takes us to a new and beautiful place but the same time it takes us through places we could never expected. My friend has spent 8 months on this project. From the day he started gathering recycled materials to the day he nailed the final piece on the house. Many doubts and internal dialogue have played into his mind. But he prevailed and created this beautiful space by the bush. Sometimes he would share this space with the people he loves. Other time it is his quiet retreat. Vietnamese Beef Pho for this rainy Melbourne evening 🍲  Recipe: 2L GF beef stock 3 thick slices ginger 1 onion, thinly sliced 3 garlic cloves, sliced 3 star anise 2 cinnamon quills, bruised 4 peppercorns 2 tbsp caster sugar 1/3 cup fish sauce 375g flat rice noodles 600g rump steak 1 cup bean sprouts 1 bunch watercress 4 spring onions, finely sliced 1/2 bunch coriander 1 red chilli, thinly sliced  1. Place stock + 500ml water in saucepan with ginger, onion, garlic, star anise, cinnamon, sugar and fish sauce 2. Bring to boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer for 30-40 mins 3. Prepare rice noodles, drain well 4. Use slotted spoon to remove ginger, garlic, cinnamon and star anise from broth 5. Season rump with salt and pepper and sear in hot pan (should be fairly rare) - allow to rest 6. Divide noodles and broth among soup bowls 7. Thinly slice rump and distribute between bowls 8. Top with bean sprouts, watercress, coriander, spring onion and chilli  Serves 4. Enjoy!!

6 WAYS I'VE CHANGED SINCE BECOMING A MUM! Well this is a pretty easy list to make so thanks @houseofwhite_ for the challenge. ➖1. No surprises here but I've learnt to completely love dry shampoo💁🏼, I CANNOT get through the week without it! Washing your hair every second day is so last decade. I far prefer a burst from a can and faking it till I make it! ➖2. Speaking of faking it till you make it. Since having kids and realising how friken bad the sun is for you I've become a seriously sun conscious mama and LOVE a fake bake. These days I won't leave the house without a 👒hat, suncream, ⛱possibly longer sleeves etc. and THIS from the girl who spent a lot of her retail wage (some years ago) on solariums and ALWAYS baked my face in the sun 😫 god help me I'll be a rotten old leather bag in a few years. ➖3. I literally look at heels these days and laugh!👟👟I am bambi at the best of times, always rolling my ankles but since having two babes and attempting heels for occasional parties I've decided that me and heels are literally on an 'occassion' basis. Give me a good solid (low) wedge for work or block heel on 'occasions' but forget about seeing me in a stiletto👠 anytime soon. ➖4. I don't give a flying 'pigs arse' about people's opinions of me like I once did. 🙅You don't agree with the way my kids are acting, the way I over share as a mother?! Disagree with the fact that we travel with our kids, think I work too much, spend too much time on social media, drink too much coffee? Well I really could care less, take your opinions & judginess elsewhere.🤦🏼‍♀️ I've got NO TIME for the bitchy, bullying type in my life.💃 ➖5. CRY BABY-😭 sharing this one with you Liv. I am now the person that sooks at a Toyota commercial, you CANNOT take me anywhere. I was literally THE person uncontrollably sobbing in the cinema watching Lion and my husband just had to sit there and bare it. ➖6. Body image, 💃I ♡ my body more today than I did pre kids. I eat a healthy primarily sugar and gluten free diet, I feel energetic and strong (due to two solid Pilates sessions at @whitedogstudiofootscray every week), <continued in comments> 👇

#DearIwashere - #noblepark . . . Ini akelo, makanan Afrika yang dibuat dari tepung dan gandum. Lucunya, di Wikipedia makanan ini nggak tertulis. Makanan Afrika yang paling mirip sama ini dan bisa kita temuin kalo googling, namanya couscous. . Tapi kata Pak Stephen Nual, juru masaknya, akelo beda sama couscous. Couscous butirannya kecil-kecil, akelo lebih besar. Meskipun sekilas nggak keliatan banyak-banyak amat, makanan ini padet banget. #IkanPaus dan Dea makan sepiring berdua abis itu kekenyangan dan nggak makan lagi seharian. Kata Pak Nual, akelo emang dimakan kalau orang mau nempuh perjalanan panjang. Biar awet. Nggak laper-laper lagi di jalan. . Kami makan akelo pake ikan dan bumbu herbal-herbalan. Tapi sebenernya akelo kayak nasi atau roti, bisa dimakan pake apa aja termasuk yoghurt, lho, @iwashere_id. . Btw, kedai Pak Nual otentik banget. Mulai dari makanan, gaya nyusun interior, sampe interaksi antar manusianya. Terus kebanyakan yang nongkrong di sana bapak-bapak. Mereka pesen satu menu besar yang dimakan rame-rame. . Kalau Dea peratiin suasana di kedai Pak Nual mirip di lapo. Bapak-bapak di sana gaya ngobrol dan becandanya entah kenapa mirip ompung-ompung. . Salamatahari, semogaselaluhangat dan cerah, Sundea . #africanfood #food #lunch #kuliner #delicious #kenyang #wareg #melbourne #latepost #knowling .

MAGANDA GLOW TERBARU  Now kami keluarkan New packaging Maganda Glow Dalam Bentuk Sachet . - 1 Kotak - 20 sachet - Formula untuk 10 / 20 hari Sahaja - 5 Gram 1 Sachet - 8x EXTRA WHITENING - 4x EXTRA COLLAGEN -Harga Rm88sm Rm99ss termasuk pos - MUDAH DIBAWA SEPERTI WALLET  KENAPA MAGANDA GLOW PACKAGING BARU 20 SACHET JE ?  JAWAPAN DIA 👇  SEBAB FORMULA DIA HANYA UNTUK 10/x 20 HARI SAHAJA .  SEBAB 8X EXTRA WHITENING DAN 4 X EXTRA COLLAGEN .  SO ANDA BOLEH CANTIK DALAM MASA YANG SINGKAT TERAPI SECARA SIHAT .  TAPI KENAPA TAK CUKUPKAN SEBULAN ?  SEBAB COLLAGEN DAH TINGGI , TAK RAMAI ANTI BODY MANUSIA YANG MAMPU MENAMPUNG EXTRA COLLAGEN .  HABIS SEKOTAK WAJIB BELI LAGI TAK ?  COLLAGEN DALAM BADAN KITA MAKIN HARI BUKAN MAKIN BERTAMBAH, TETAPI MAKIN BERKURANG , SEBAB ITU ANDA HARUS AMALKAN MAKANAN BERCOLLAGEN TETAPI DENGAN MAGANDA GLOW ANDA HANYA BELI BILA ANDA PERLU SAHAJA , TAK PERLU REPEAT SETIAP BULAN KERANA KAMI DAH EXTRAKAN COLLAGEN KEPADA ANDA.  MAKSUD? Contoh dah habis 1 kotak ? Anda tidak pelru terburu-buru untk terus repeat atau continues seperti product lain..anda boleh stop dlu tetapi kulit tetap cantik , cerah dan sihat . We have said it before, but walking tours really are great for seeing a city in a short space of time. It was a sunny day in Melbourne, so pretty busy, but we were still able to learn a lot about the city's history. Favourite facts:  1- Melbourne 'conveniently' found gold about two weeks after separating from Sydney, which arguably triggered their rivalry, particularly as Melbourne subsequently became the richest city in the world during the 1880s gold rush.  2- Melbourne has not one, but two bank holidays for sporting events. The Melbourne Cup and AFL Grand Final both merit a day off work!  After the historical section, we also had chance to see the contemporary side of the city, including the legal street art, independent eateries and many arts buildings.

Last night we were lucky enough to be taken to a local kushi katsu (deep fried skewers) restaurant by a good friend from my Tokyo Tina days.  This gem of deep fried goodness blew our minds, after talking to the owner we found out the place has been open for 44 years doing the same type of deep fried skewers and only being able to sit a maximum of 8 people at one time.  Watching her cook methodically, clean and entertain us as she was the only one the in the kitchen was simply amazing. She reminded me of Mr Miyagi, friendly and always up for a laugh but a master of her craft 😂

Every exercise in your program must serve a purpose... - Ask yourself: why am I performing X movement? - If you are performing any exercise for the hell of it, without a specific reason, then you're simply adding 'junk volume' to your training. - When training for strength and size, it is important to remember that every exercise in your program can either benefit or detriment your progress. Training for the sake of training or filling up time not only reduces your training economy (time wasting), but it may slow down your progress as a result of additional fatigue, which maybe unnecessary. - Take the hip thrust for example... It can: 1. Teach hip extension. 2. Add volume for the posterior chain - aka bigger and stronger glutes. 3. Serve rehab purposes. - Performing any exercise just because is a sure way to slow your progress, so make sure that everything you do in the gym can be justified! - #TeamJPS  #RaisingTheStandard - #bodybuilding #powerlifting #fitness #strength #strong #lift #gym #physique #training #lean #muscle #squat #bench #abs #ripped #aesthetic #deadlift #lean #iifym #flexibledieting #inspiration #motivation #muscle #results #personaltrainer #melbourne #portmelbourne #airportwest #portmelbournebeach

The staff at Il Duca were most helpful and attentive without being intrusive. We thoroughly enjoyed the evening and look forward to returning to Il Duca in the near future. 10/10'. . . Use Mondays to kick off the week with a clear head and clear goals in mind whether they're food or training focused. The Peacock Inn was the second hotel to open in Northcote after the Pilgrim Inn Hotel (now the Croxton Park). In its early days it was a common haunt for teamsters and draymen travelling to and from Northcote's brickworks. The Age reported in July 1937, a George Harvey of North Fitzroy was charged with illegal bookmaking in the pub's garage, averaging around 300 bets on race days. He was represented at court by John Galbally, a Collingwood footballer and founder of the law firm Galbally & O'Bryan. A happy gut is at the root of good health and our general wellbeing. It makes a sh*tload of sense when you think about it. The gut can ‘think' and act independent of the brain - it's the only organ with those special powers and part of the reason why it’s been labelled our 'second brain’. It's home to more than 100 million brain cells and around 95% of the body’s serotonin. With the gut being to closely linked to our mood, it only seems logical that we nourish it with foods that help it thrive. My top tips to keep your gut on side:  1. Take a daily probiotic 2. Add fermented foods to your meals or eat/drink these things separately daily (add kimchi, miso and/or tempeh to your salads, add kefir to your breakfast or have it as a snack, drink diluted apple cider vinegar first thing in the morning etc.) 3. Avoid over-consumption of alcohol. 4. Chew your food throughly to aid digestion. 5. Eat plenty of plant-based fibre. 📷🌱 @kitchenofamelia . . . . .

Back Development:  To grow a thick and complete back a combination of exercises are needed. Heavy rows or heavy deadlifts are favourites of mine as they build thickness like no other. .  However to complete your back development more targeted exercises are necessary too. .  To build the width nothing beats a stiff arm pull down, you can get a huge range of motion and even bigger contraction through your lats when done correctly. .  Then to build the finer detail, nothing beats for me a unilateral (singe hand) row, this could be on a cable machine or a plate loaded machine or even with a dumbbell. They all work great! . Another burger post guyssss!! So a couple weeks ago when Melbourne decided to not be bipolar and give us a full day of sun so a friend and I decided to go smash a couple burgers. Not really knowing this side of town 100% yet and where the delicious burgers are located she suggested the infamous Fat Bob's @fatbobsbarandgrill in Moorabbin. This place is hidden away in sort of an industrial area but it was super packed and it made me excited, because a busy burger place is a good burger place!! Fat Bob's is an American style diner with a large range of burgers with a load more sides!! I ended up getting the Red Dog (double beef burger with extra Fat Bob's sauce) and she got some onion rings and some popcorn chicken!! And man when they came out my mouth was watering!! When the burger came out I was so hungry I nearly forgot to take a photo for you guys! It was super tasty and the flavour was really nice! The sides of onion rings and popcorn chicken was a bonus, they made the meal so much better, I should have gotten a milkshake to finish it off though, but there's always next time ;). Great service, great atmosphere and quick to table burgers to! I give it a solid 7.5/10🍔🍔, what a great way to finish off a beautiful  Melbourne day  Thanks @fatbobsbarandgrill for the big dirty burger! And see you guys again soon :) #fatbobsburgerandgrill #burgers #burgersfortheboys #doublepattie #reddog #macandcheese #burgersofmelbourne #melbourne #melbournefood #moorabbin #theburgercollective

Ferris wheel- Australia  The London Eye has really made Ferris wheels fashionable these days. When I saw it for the first time I was very impressed but somehow this has become the defining feature in many international cities and even though they look nice, I am kind of bored of these. I purchase a very expensive ticket to experience thw London Eye but it was the slowest 45 minutes of my life. My brother in law slept on the bench. Even though the view was mind blowing I still thought that I could you spent in those quids in a bar on beer and enjoyed much. I have seen the Ferris Wheel in many cities such as Singapore, Shanghai, a city called tianjin in China, in Germany, Melbourne, Maine USA and so on and so forth. These are definitely not restricted to theme parks anymore and I'm not spending on them. . . .  #roadtrippin #roadtrip #melbourne #vic #aus #australia #scenicdrive #wanderlust #globetrotter #insta #instagood #instagram #greatoceanroad #travelstyle #travel #travels #travelphotography #travelph #picoftheday #instago #ferriswheel #londoneye

This cold wet night needed something comforting and warm and a chocolate self saucing pudding delivered.  What made this even more was a raspberry buttermilk and yoghurt ice cream (can I call it that?) that took it to the next level. See the #icecream was made with 2 drops of citrus fresh eo. This blend of Orange, Grapefruit, Mandarin, Tangerine, Lemon, and Spearmint pairs with raspberries so well giving an almost fruit tingle flavour. Serving it with pudding cut through the sweetness of the chocolate , was delicious and will definitely be on high rotation this autumn / winter ❄️ 🍂

When I first started practising yoga it was merely something to do with my spare time whilst instructing in Japan. The way I felt as I walked out of the studio is what kept me going back. And now, I practice nearly every day! Having just arrived home from my season in the states, I thought I'd treat myself to a brand spankin' @lululemonausnz mat. No regrets.  __________________________________________________________ Whilst training for my level 3, my trainers helped me understand just how beneficial yoga is for our skiing. Not only does it help to take care of our muscles and joints, it improves flexibility and core strength, and also leaves you feeling mentally refreshed & ready to attack the day!

Rolling over those tight spots and knots is a form of self-massage that increases blood flow to muscles and helps rid lactic acid, which is really important for recovery and improving mobility overall. You can foam roll pre or post-workout and you'll notice its benefits and positive impacts on your training pretty quickly if you stick at it. 📷 @kayla_itsines . . . .

Walking is a great way to boost your physical activity – and your body will thank you in more ways than one. Energising, versatile and low-impact, walking is a great choice for anyone wanting to fit more physical cavity into their daily life. It can be done anytime and anywhere, and it’s something that most people can do regardless of age or starting fitness levels. Plus, there are plenty of opportunities you can find to fit walking into your day, without necessarily thinking of it as exercise. Here are just some of the health benefits of walking… 1. It can make you live longer Well, that’s just about the ultimate health benefit, isn’t it? Regular physical activity improves your chances of living a longer, healthier life, and a Harvard University study suggested that walking briskly for just 75 minutes a week can add almost two years to your life, while upping your steps to walk 2.5 hours a week can add more than seven years.  2. It helps keep your heart healthy Being active helps keep your heart in good condition. To reduce your risk of heart disease and high blood pressure, the Heart Foundation suggests aiming for 30 minutes of moderate activity such as walking on most if not all days of the week, if not all, and studies show that when it comes to cardiovascular health, a solid, brisk walk is as good as a run. People who walk regularly have fewer heart attacks and strokes, have lower blood pressure, and higher levels of healthy HDL cholesterol than those who are mostly sedentary. 3. It reduces your risk of diabetes A combination of daily exercise, a balanced diet and a healthy body weight can prevent 60% of type 2 diabetes cases. Regular walking is a great way to manage your weight, and therefore reduce your chances of developing this common condition. Plus, walking for 30 minutes a day makes your muscles more sensitive to insulin, which means betterblood sugar control– which not only helps lower your risk of diabetes, it can also help you to manage the condition if you already have it. 4. It helps you lose and manage weight - what more incentive do you need :)

Just an Old-World writer trying to return the world's attention from platitudinous feelgoodery and colouring books to intricately crafted, elegantly hilarious novels. — He seldom wears pants, he seldomer wears a shirt. This is partly because he is unwealthy and doesn't want to wear out the fabric, partly because he is stuck in a very warm place. — He was supposed to be a lawyer. Instead he studied history and has recently chosen to drive himself insane by attempting to create a new form of novel—a work of art that is both thoroughly elegant and incomparably entertaining. The Comedy Novel. — He expects, but does not recoil from, the eventuality that the unremitting pursuit of the comedy novel will drive him to hugging horses and asking boys to hold his hand during thunderstorms. But he is not afraid. His little vocation of writing books makes him thoroughly content. — Now marooned in Southeast Asia, his considerable mental energies are bent towards gaining a wide enough readership to enable him to write his next novel, for which he has already begun compiling notes. — So, GRIEVE is now available to pre-order. — The book took him a year to write. Most of you have followed him on that journey. Now, make no mistake... You are his audience. IG is hisbreadership. He has no PR team. No distribution deal. He does everything myself. From writing to editing to launching. The books are then yours, as he sends them out into the world. — And each time you double tap and move on, or leave a love-heart-eyes emoticon—a butterfly gets a degenerative wing disorder. — I am not here to post pictures of protein powder or my dinner, or of leg day or puppies. I am here to write novels. Elegantly hilarious novels. Your reading them is truly the only thing that keeps me going. — Pre-orders for GRIEVE are now open. — Pre-order an inscribed copy now,  at 🦌 joshvahvmphreys.com — #joshwritebook #comedynovel #GRIEVE

In the spirit of the season, I've been contemplating freedom. Last night's Seder, a six course meal for 22 people. Two days in the kitchen and then the mayhem of the meal. Even the 9 year old noted "it was like I was caged". What actually is freedom? My life is a charmed one. Freedom to make choices, determine my path, to do mainly as I please. But what of those who live under oppressive regimes, those whose lives are characterised by restriction, inequity, disadvantage? After 20 years working in human rights I know freedom to be a hard won right, yet still, for so many, it's not there, not even here, in this seemingly free bountiful country. Such a complicated world. So many questions, so much injustice. This Passover, I meditate on peace and on freedom 🙏 #yoga #yogagirl #yogi #yogalove #yogateacher #yogaeverydamnday #yogaeverywhere  #instayoga #yogisofig #om #yogainspiration #melbournelovesyoga #yogapractice #asana #yogaaddict #breath #mindfulness #awareness #meditation #movement  #melbourne #life #autumn #wellness #health #passover #peseach #freedom

A kookaburra laughs at the break of dawn, and a magpie returns his song. The sun slowly rises above the clouds, the morning has just begun. - With every breath I take, my sole is cleansed, my problems gone.  I'm am flying freely in this hour, running from all that is now gone. - The cool mist hits my face, with the gentle smells of home. The childhood memories of walking these paths, when I was not alone. - The red earth broken beneath the wattles, the leaves of the peppermint gums. These smells are so addictive, like earth is beating its drums. - Its rhythm beckons my return tomorrow and next. Today I was walking down the street struggling & feeling upset about leaving Melbourne in less than 2 weeks... I was questioning the sacrifices that it sometimes feels like I'm making in order to fulfil my Soul Purpose & talking with @aaronmoonc about it when I almost walked into this sign... .
